tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and low urine specific gravity, indicating impaired renal function. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal odor, ketonuria, proteinuria, glucosuria) suggest possible renal pathology, dehydration, or metabolic disturbance. Low HbA1c with normoglycemia may reflect recent hypoglycemia or anemia. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and metabolic status.
